definition:
A woman of the tribe of Judah living at the time of United Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ki.4.15; 
 daughter of: Solomon (H8010); 
 sister of: Taphath (H2955) and Rehoboam (H7346); married to Ahimaaz (H0290I)
 § Bashemath or Basmath = "spice"
1) Hittite wife of Esau, daughter of Ishmael, sister of Nebaioth
2) daughter of Solomon, wife of Ahimaaz, one of Solomon's commissariat officers
